            <div class="article" style="text-align:justify">
                Elderly abuse in nursing homes refers to the injuries suffered by the elderly in nursing homes, including physical abuse, mental abuse, sexual abuse, financial abuse and Nursing home neglect. These abuses may be caused by co-residents, relatives or caregivers.<br>
                According to experimental estimates by the Office of the Royal Commission into Aged Care Quality and Safety (2020), about 39.2 percent of people living in Australian aged care facilities experience elder abuse.<br><br><br><br>
