            <div class="article" style="text-align:justify">
                There are five types of nursing home elder abuse: physical abuse, mental abuse, sexual abuse, financial abuse, and Nursing home neglect. When the staff of nursing homes, other residents, or relatives of the elderly deliberately cause harm to the elderly, they are committing abuse.<br>
                Among these types of elder abuse, it is estimated that 30.8% of the elderly have experienced neglect, 22.6% have experienced mental abuse, and 5% have experienced physical abuse ("Elder Abuse in Australian Aged Care Facilities", 2021).
            </div>
